<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9441] Solr collection backup on HDFS can only be manipulated by the Solr process owner</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9441</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we backup Solr collection using HDFS backup repository, the backup folder (and the files) are created with permissions 755 (i.e. only solr process owner can delete/move the backup folder). This is inconvenient from user perspective since the backup is essentially a full-copy of the Solr collection and hence manipulating it doesn&apos;t affect the Solr collection state in any way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should provide an option by which we can enable other users to manipulate the backup folders. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
